# Git LFS Configuration for Large Files
# Uncomment lines below if you want to use Git LFS for video files

# Track all video files in public/videos/ with Git LFS
# public/videos/*.mp4 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# public/videos/*.webm filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# public/videos/*.mov filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# To enable Git LFS:
# 1. Install Git LFS: https://git-lfs.github.com/
# 2. Run: git lfs install
# 3. Uncomment the lines above
# 4. Run: git add .gitattributes
# 5. Add your videos: git add public/videos/
# 6. Commit and push

# Note: Without Git LFS, keep videos under 100MB each
# For larger videos, use YouTube embeds instead
